context: In June 1854, the Allied expeditionary force landed at Varna, a city on the Black Sea's <a0_0>western coast<a0_0/> (now in Bulgaria). They made little advance from their base there.:175–176 In July 1854, the Turks under <a1_0>Omar Pasha<a1_0/> crossed the Danube into Wallachia and on 7 July <a2_0>1854<a2_0/>, engaged the Russians in the city of <a3_0>Giurgiu<a3_0/> and conquered it. The capture of Giurgiu by the Turks immediately threatened Bucharest in Wallachia with capture by the same Turk army. On 26 July 1854, <a4_0>Tsar Nicholas I<a4_0/> ordered the withdrawal of Russian troops from the Principalities.
